<br>
<br>
Ok, my little tip of the day. I do not remember where I saw this, but since I started doing it, my life has been much easier. Bind your 9th and 10th hotkey slots to the same keys as what you use for moving left and right. Then, put sense heading in both of those slots. That way, every time you turn left or right, you use the skill. It makes it max out so easily that you would not believe it. If you feel you need those 2 slots, then make a second page for doing this. Just remember to unbind the keys when you aren ot using this method. Sense heading is NOT a skill to put points into. It is too easy to skill up without it. <p>      <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Love is the answer; but while you're waiting for the answer, sex raises some pretty good questions.&quot; (Woody Allen) </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/03 3:16:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=63>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Training points</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Bind your 9th and 10th hotkey slots to the same keys as what you use for moving left and right. Then, put sense heading in both of those sl